{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-bfff1089afe313b7", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# Raon-OpenTTS: Open Models and Data for Robust Text-to-Speech\narXiv: 2605.20830\nAuthors: Semin Kim, Seungjun Chung, Taehong Moon, Sangheon Lee, Minyoung Ahn, Keon Lee, Nam Soo Kim, Jaewoong Cho, Ludwig Schmidt, Kangwook Lee, Dongmin Park\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce Raon-OpenTTS-Pool, a 615K-hour English speech corpus aggregated from publicly available sources and web-sourced recordings, which is the largest openly available multi-source dataset curated for TTS training to our knowledge.\n  2. We derive Raon-OpenTTS-Core, a filtered subset of 510K hours and 194M speech segments from Raon-OpenTTS-Pool, and show that training on it consistently improves zero-shot TTS performance over the unfiltered pool.\n  3. We introduce Raon-OpenTTS-Eval, a robustness-oriented evaluation benchmark spanning four acoustic regimes with 6K prompt-text pairs, enabling systematic analysis of zero-shot TTS across diverse real-world conditions.\n  4. We release Raon-OpenTTS, a DiT-based TTS model family with 0.3B and 1B parameters, which ranks first or second in word error rate and speaker similarity among recent open-weight zero-shot TTS baselines while remaining competitive with models trained on large-scale proprietary data.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/功能-DiT\n====\nPaper 2603.14873 not found", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "9a96c89b-4885-4364-8a16-c1abd1c85afd", "uuid": "e89ad285-1e3e-4151-b880-d4c34989f409", "timestamp": "2026-07-07T07:41:53.880Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# Raon-OpenTTS: Open Models and Data for Robust Text-to-Speech\narXiv: 2605.20830\nAuthors: Semin Kim, Seungjun Chung, Taehong Moon, Sangheon Lee, Minyoung Ahn, Keon Lee, Nam Soo Kim, Jaewoong Cho, Ludwig Schmidt, Kangwook Lee, Dongmin Park\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce Raon-OpenTTS-Pool, a 615K-hour English speech corpus aggregated from publicly available sources and web-sourced recordings, which is the largest openly available multi-source dataset curated for TTS training to our knowledge.\n  2. We derive Raon-OpenTTS-Core, a filtered subset of 510K hours and 194M speech segments from Raon-OpenTTS-Pool, and show that training on it consistently improves zero-shot TTS performance over the unfiltered pool.\n  3. We introduce Raon-OpenTTS-Eval, a robustness-oriented evaluation benchmark spanning four acoustic regimes with 6K prompt-text pairs, enabling systematic analysis of zero-shot TTS across diverse real-world conditions.\n  4. We release Raon-OpenTTS, a DiT-based TTS model family with 0.3B and 1B parameters, which ranks first or second in word error rate and speaker similarity among recent open-weight zero-shot TTS baselines while remaining competitive with models trained on large-scale proprietary data.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/功能-DiT\n====\nPaper 2603.14873 not found", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
